                  <summary>The document&amp;apos;s chief interest resides in its mention of a Ceasarium built at Antinoopolis. This information, while hardly surprising, is new. In Egypt Caesarea are recorded also at Alexandria, Arsinoe, Hermopolis and Oxyrhynchos.  The petitioners ask for their salry for the month Phamenoth.</summary>
